quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  27,1,"Tâ Sîn. Those are the signs{1}of the Recital{2}and an Evident Scripture—",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used isayat(singularayah). Ayahmeans ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Qur’an,like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose.Each such unit isconsidered a ‘sign’from God.|2:The Arabic word used is Qur’an which means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  27,2,"guidance and glad tidings for the believers"
  27,3,"who establish the prayer and bring{1}the purifying charity{2}and, of the Hereafter, they are certain.",footnotes:1:The Qur’an always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’ in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.|2:The Arabic word used is zakāt, which denotes purification and growth.
  27,4,"Indeed, those who do not believe in the Hereafter—We have adorned their deeds for them, so they wander aimlessly;"
  27,5,"those are the ones for whom is the worst punishment, and in the Hereafter they are the biggest losers."
  27,6,"And indeed, you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>are surely receiving the Recital<a class=""sup""><sup>b </sup></a>from One who is All-Wise, All-Knowing."
  27,7,"Recall when Moses said to his family, “I have surely glimpsed a fire. I will bring you some news from it, or bring you a <span class=""h"">firebrand, a borrowed flame<sup foot_note=""80735"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, that you may warm yourselves.”"
  27,8,"Then when he reached it, he was called: “Blessed is whoever is in the fire and whoever is around it, and Highly Exalted is Allah, Lord of all realms."
  27,9,"O Moses, it is indeed I, Allah, the Almighty, the All-Wise."
  27,10,"Now, cast your staff.” So when he saw it shaking as though it were a snake, he turned away, fleeing, and did not look back. “O Moses, fear not! Truly, in My presence emissaries have nothing to fear,"
  27,11,"except for one who did an injustice then substituted kindness for evil—then I am surely Oft-Forgiving, Bestowing of mercy."
  27,12,"And put your hand inside the opening of your garment<i class=""s"">(and) </i>it will come out white, without any evil affliction—among nine signs to Pharaoh and his people; they have indeed been a defiantly disobedient people.”"
  27,13,"So when Our signs came to them as an eye-opener, they said, “This is evident sorcery.”"
